e</a></th>\n<td><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%2B255\" title=\"+255\" class=\"mw-redirect\">+255</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-c_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tanzania#cite_note-c-11\"><span>[</span>note 1<span>]</span></a></sup></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"mergedtoprow\">\n<th colspan=\"2\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166\" title=\"ISO 3166\">ISO 3166 code</a></th>\n<td><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-2:TZ\" title=\"ISO 3166-2:TZ\">TZ</a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"2\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Country_code_top-level_domain\" title=\"Country code top-level domain\">Internet TLD</a></th>\n<td><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/.tz\" title=\".tz\">.tz</a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"font-size:85%;\">\n<td align=\"right\"><span style=\"position: relative; top: 0.3em;\"><sup>a.</sup></span></td>\n<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"padding-left:0;\">Revised to $41.33 billion<sup id=\"cite_ref-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tanzania#cite_note-12\"><span>[</span>11<span>]</span></a></sup></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<p><b>Tanzania</b> <span class=\"nowrap\"><span title=\"Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)\" class=\"IPA\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\">/</a></span><span class=\"IPA nopopups\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\"><span title=\"/ˌ/ secondary stress follows\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">ˌ</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA nopopups\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\"><span title=\"\'t\' in \'tie\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">t</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA nopopups\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\"><span title=\"/æ/ short \'a\' in \'bad\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">æ</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA nopopups\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\"><span title=\"\'n\' in \'nigh\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">n</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA nopopups\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\"><span title=\"\'z\' in \'zebra\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">z</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA nopopups\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\"><span title=\"/ə/ \'a\' in \'about\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">ə</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA nopopups\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\"><span title=\"/ˈ/ primary stress follows\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">ˈ</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA nopopups\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\"><span title=\"\'n\' in \'nigh\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">n</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA nopopups\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\"><span title=\"/iː/ long \'e\' in \'bead\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">iː</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA nopopups\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\"><span title=\"/ə/ \'a\' in \'about\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">ə</span></a></span><span title=\"Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)\" class=\"IPA\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\">/</a></span></span>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-13\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tanzania#cite_note-13\"><span>[</span>12<span>]</span></a></sup> officially the <b>United Republic of Tanzania</b> (<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swahili_language\" title=\"Swahili language\">Swahili</a>: <span lang=\"sw\"><i>Jamhuri ya Muungano wa Tanzania</i></span>), is a country in <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/East_Africa\" title=\"East Africa\">East Africa</a> within the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/African_Great_Lakes\" title=\"African Great Lakes\">African Great Lakes</a> region. It is bordered by <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kenya\" title=\"Kenya\">Kenya</a> and <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uganda\" title=\"Uganda\">Uganda</a> to the north; <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rwanda\" title=\"Rwanda\">Rwanda</a>, <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Burundi\" title=\"Burundi\">Burundi</a>, and the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Democratic_Republic_of_the_Congo\" title=\"Democratic Republic of the Congo\">Democratic Republic of the Congo</a> to the west; <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zambia\" title=\"Zambia\">Zambia</a>, <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Malawi\" title=\"Malawi\">Malawi</a>, and <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mozambique\" title=\"Mozambique\">Mozambique</a> to the south; and the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indian_Ocean\" title=\"Indian Ocean\">Indian Ocean</a> to the east. <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kilimanjaro\" title=\"Kilimanjaro\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Kilimanjaro</a>, Africa\'s highest mountain, is in northeastern Tanzania.</p>\n<p>Tanzania\'s population of 44.9 million is highly diverse, composed of numerous ethnic, linguistic, and religious groups. Islam is biggest religion followed by Christianity. Tanzania is a presidential constitutional republic, and since 1996, its official capital has been <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dodoma\" title=\"Dodoma\">Dodoma</a>, where the President\'s Office, the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Assembly_(Tanzania)\" title=\"National Assembly (Tanzania)\">National Assembly</a>, and some government ministries are located.<sup id=\"cite_ref-14\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tanzania#cite_note-14\"><span>[</span>13<span>]</span></a></sup> <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dar_es_Salaam\" title=\"Dar es Salaam\">Dar es Salaam</a>, the former capital, retains most government offices and is the country\'s largest city, principal port, and leading commercial center.<sup id=\"cite_ref-factbook_15-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tanzania#cite_note-factbook-15\"><span>[</span>14<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-official_website_16-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tanzania#cite_note-official_website-16\"><span>[</span>15<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-17\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tanzania#cite_note-17\"><span>[</span>16<span>]</span></a></sup></p>\n<p>European colonialism began in mainland Tanzania during the late 19th century when Germany formed <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/German_East_Africa\" title=\"German East Africa\">German East Africa</a>, which gave way to British rule following <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_War_I\" title=\"World War I\">World War I</a>. The mainland was governed as <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tanganyika\" title=\"Tanganyika\">Tanganyika</a>, with the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zanzibar_Archipelago\" title=\"Zanzibar Archipelago\">Zanzibar Archipelago</a> remaining a separate colonial jurisdiction. Following their respective independence in 1961 and 1963, the two entities merged in April 1964 to form the United Republic of Tanzania.<sup id=\"cite_ref-factbook_15-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tanzania#cite_note-factbook-15\"><span>[</span>14<span>]</span></a></sup></p>\n<p></p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\">\n<div id=\"toctitle\"'),(64,NULL,'Germany',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-21 19:45:37',NULL),(65