itle=\"Coordinated Universal Time\">UTC</a>+2)</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"2\">Drives on the</th>\n<td><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Right-_and_left-hand_traffic\" title=\"Right- and left-hand traffic\">left</a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"2\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Telephone_numbers_in_Swaziland\" title=\"Telephone numbers in Swaziland\">Calling code</a></th>\n<td><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%2B268\" title=\"+268\" class=\"mw-redirect\">+268</a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"mergedtoprow\">\n<th colspan=\"2\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166\" title=\"ISO 3166\">ISO 3166 code</a></th>\n<td><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-2:SZ\" title=\"ISO 3166-2:SZ\">SZ</a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"2\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Country_code_top-level_domain\" title=\"Country code top-level domain\">Internet TLD</a></th>\n<td><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/.sz\" title=\".sz\">.sz</a></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<p><b>Swaziland</b>, officially the <b>Kingdom of Swaziland</b> (<span class=\"nowrap\"><span title=\"Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)\" class=\"IPA\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\">/</a></span><span class=\"IPA nopopups\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\"><span title=\"\'s\' in \'sigh\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">s</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA nopopups\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\"><span title=\"\'w\' in \'wind\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">w</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA nopopups\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\"><span title=\"/ɑː/ \'a\' in \'spa\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">ɑː</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA nopopups\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\"><span title=\"\'z\' in \'zebra\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">z</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA nopopups\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\"><span title=\"/ɨ/ \'e\' in \'roses\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">ɨ</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA nopopups\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\"><span title=\"\'l\' in \'lie\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">l</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA nopopups\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\"><span title=\"/æ/ short \'a\' in \'bad\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">æ</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA nopopups\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\"><span title=\"\'n\' in \'nigh\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">n</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA nopopups\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\"><span title=\"\'d\' in \'dye\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">d</span></a></span><span title=\"Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)\" class=\"IPA\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\">/</a></span></span> or <span class=\"nowrap\"><span title=\"Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)\" class=\"IPA\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\">/</a></span><span class=\"IPA nopopups\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\"><span title=\"\'s\' in \'sigh\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">s</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA nopopups\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\"><span title=\"\'w\' in \'wind\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">w</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA nopopups\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\"><span title=\"/ɑː/ \'a\' in \'spa\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">ɑː</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA nopopups\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\"><span title=\"\'z\' in \'zebra\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">z</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA nopopups\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\"><span title=\"/ɨ/ \'e\' in \'roses\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">ɨ</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA nopopups\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\"><span title=\"\'l\' in \'lie\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">l</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA nopopups\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\"><span title=\"/ə/ \'a\' in \'about\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">ə</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA nopopups\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\"><span title=\"\'n\' in \'nigh\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">n</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA nopopups\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\"><span title=\"\'d\' in \'dye\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">d</span></a></span><span title=\"Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)\" class=\"IPA\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English\" title=\"Help:IPA for English\">/</a></span></span>; <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swazi_language\" title=\"Swazi language\">Swazi</a>: <i>Umbuso weSwatini</i> ; sometimes called <b>kaNgwane</b> or <b>Eswatini</b><sup id=\"cite_ref-Spch2014_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swaziland#cite_note-Spch2014-4\"><span>[</span>4<span>]</span></a></sup>) is a <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sovereign_state\" title=\"Sovereign state\">sovereign state</a> in <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Southern_Africa\" title=\"Southern Africa\">Southern Africa</a>. It is neighbored by <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mozambique\" title=\"Mozambique\">Mozambique</a> to its east and by <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Africa\" title=\"South Africa\">South Africa</a> to its north, west and south. The country and its <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swazi_people\" title=\"Swazi people\">people</a> take their names from <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mswati_II\" title=\"Mswati II\">Mswati II</a>, the 19th-century king under whose rule Swazi territory was expanded and unified.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Kuper86_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swaziland#cite_note-Kuper86-5\"><span>[</span>5<span>]</span></a></sup></p>\n<p>At no more than 200 kilometres (120&#160;mi) north to south and 130 kilometres (81&#160;mi) east to west, Swaziland is one of the smallest countries in Africa. Despite its size, however, its climate and <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Topography\" title=\"Topography\">topography</a> is diverse, ranging from a cool and mountainous <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Highveld\" title=\"Highveld\">highveld</a> to a hot and dry <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Veld#Lowveld\" title=\"Veld\">lowveld</a>. The population is primarily ethnic <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swazi_people\" title=\"Swazi people\">Swazis</a> whose language is <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swati_language\" title=\"Swati language\" class=\"mw-redirect\">siSwati</a>. They established their kingdom in the mid-18th century under the leadership of <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ngwane_III\" title=\"Ngwane III\">Ngwane III</a>; the present boundaries were drawn up in 1881.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Bonner82_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swaziland#cite_note-Bonner82-6\"><span>[</span>6<span>]</span></a></sup> After the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anglo-Boer_War\" title=\"Anglo-Boer War\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Anglo-Boer War</a>, Swaziland was a <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Kingdom_of_Great_Britain_and_Ireland\" title=\"United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland\">British</a> <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Protectorate\" title=\"Protectorate\">protectorate</a> from 1903 until 1967. It regained its independence on 6 September 1968.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Gillis99_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swaziland#cite_note-Gillis99-7\"><span>[</span>7<span>]</span></a></sup></p>\n<p>The country is an <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Absolute_monarchy\" title=\"Absolute monarchy\">absolute monarchy</a>, currently ruled by <i><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ngwenyama\" title=\"Ngwenyama\">Ngwenyama</a></i> (\"King\") <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mswati_III\" title=\"Mswati III\">Mswati III</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swaziland#cite_note-8\"><span>[</span>8<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swaziland#cite_note-9\"><span>[</span>9<span>]</span></a></sup> He is <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Head_of_state\" title=\"Head of state\">head of state</a> and appoints the country\'s prime minister and a number of representatives of both chambers (<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Senate_of_Swaziland\" title=\"Senate of Swaziland\">Senate</a> and <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/House_of_Assembly_of_Swaziland\" title=\"House of Assembly of Swaziland\">House of Assembly</a>) in <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parliament_of_Swaziland\" title=\"Parliament of Swaziland\">the country\'s parliament</a>. Elections are held every five years to determine the House of Assembly majority. The current <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constitution_of_Swaziland\" title=\"Constitution of Swaziland\" class=\"mw-redirect\">constitution</a> was adopted in 2005.</p>\n<p>Swaziland is a <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Developing_country\" title=\"Developing country\">developing country</a> with a small economy. Its <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gross_domestic_product\" title=\"Gross domestic product\">GDP per capita</a> of $6,367 means it is classified as a country with a lower-middle income.<sup id=\"cite_ref-imf2_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swaziland#cite_note-imf2-1\"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> As a member of the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Southern_African_Customs_Union\" title=\"Southern African Customs Union\">Southern African Customs Union</a> (SACU) and <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Common_Market_for_Eastern_and_Southern_Africa\" title=\"Common Market for Eastern and Southern Africa\">Common Market for Eastern and Southern Africa</a> (COMESA), its main local trading partner is South Africa. Swazilands currency, the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swazi_lilangeni\" title=\"Swazi lilangeni\">lilangeni</a>, is <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fixed_exchange-rate_system\" title=\"Fixed exchange-rate system\">pegged</a> to the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_African_rand\" title=\"South African rand\">South African rand</a>. Swaziland\'s major overseas trading partners are the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States\" title=\"United States\">United States</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swaziland#cite_note-10\"><span>[</span>10<span>]</span></a></sup> and the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/European_Union\" title=\"European Union\">European Union</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swaziland#cite_note-11\"><span>[</span>11<span>]</span></a></sup> The majority of the country\'s employment is provided by its agricultural and manufacturing sectors. Swaziland is a member of the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Southern_African_Development_Community\" title=\"Southern African Development Community\">Southern African Development Community</a>, the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/African_Union\" title=\"African Union\">African Union</a> and the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Commonwealth_of_Nations\" title=\"Commonwealth of Nations\">Commonwealth of Nations</a>.</p>\n<p>The Swazi population faces major health issues: <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HIV/AIDS\" title=\"HIV/AIDS\">HIV/AIDS</a> and, to a lesser extent, <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tuberculosis\" title=\"Tuberculosis\">tuberculosis</a> are serious challenges.<sup id=\"cite_ref-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swaziland#cite_note-12\"><span>[</span>12<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-13\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swaziland#cite_note-13\"><span>[</span>13<span>]</span></a></sup> As of 2013, Swaziland has an estimated life expectancy of 50 years.<sup id=\"cite_ref-rank_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swaziland#cite_note-rank-14\"><span>[</span>14<span>]</span></a></sup> The population of Swaziland is fairly young with a <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Median_age\" title=\"Median age\" class=\"mw-redirect\">median age</a> of 20.5 years and people aged 14 years or younger constituting 37.4% of the country\'s total population.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Demo_15-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swaziland#cite_note-Demo-15\"><span>[</span>15<span>]</span></a></sup> The present population growth rate is 1.195%.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Demo_15-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swaziland#cite_note-Demo-15\"><span>[</span>15<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-16\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swaziland#cite_note-16\"><span>[</span>16<span>]</span></a></sup></p>\n<p>Swaziland is well known for its culture.<sup id=\"cite_ref-17\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swaziland#cite_note-17\"><span>[</span>17<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-18\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swaziland#cite_note-18\"><span>[</span>18<span>]</span></a></sup> <i><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Umhlanga_(ceremony)\" title=\"Umhlanga (ceremony)\">Umhlanga</a></i>, held in August/September<sup id=\"cite_ref-19\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swaziland#cite_note-19\"><span>[</span>19<span>]</span></a></sup> and <i><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Incwala\" title=\"Incwala\">incwala</a></i>, the kingship dance held in December/January, are the nation\'s most important events.<sup id=\"cite_ref-20\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swaziland#cite_note-20\"><span>[</span>20<span>]</span></a></sup></p>\n<p></p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\">\n<div id=\"toctitle\"'),(184,NULL,'Benin',NULL,'upload/Benin.txt',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-25 13:39:32','	<h1 id=\"firstHeading\" class=\"firstHeading\">Benin</h1>\n		<div id=\"bodyContent\">\n			<h3 id=\"siteSub\"></h3>\n			<div id=\"contentSub\"></div>\n									<div id=\"jump-to-nav\">Jump to: <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Benin#column-one\">navigation</a>, <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Benin#searchInput\">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->\n			<div class=\"dablink\">For other uses, see <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Benin_(disambiguation)\" title=\"Benin (disambiguation)\">Benin (disambiguation)</a>.</div>\n<t